SIMPLE: pregnant
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pregnant
<hw>Preg"nant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praegnans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>; <ets>prae</ets> before +
<ets>genere</ets>, <ets>gignere</ets>, to beget: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧gnant</ets>. See <er>Gender</er>, 2d
<er>Kin</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Being with young, as a female; having conceived;
great with young; breeding; teeming; gravid; preparing to bring
forth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Heavy with important contents, significance, or
issue; full of consequence or results; weighty; <as>as,
<ex>pregnant</ex> replies</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ A <xex>pregnant</xex>
argument.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Prynne.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧ A <xex>pregnant</xex>
brevity.⟦rdquo⟧<-- pregnant silence --> <rj><au>E.
Everett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Full of promise; abounding in ability, resources,
etc.; <as>as, a <ex>pregnant</ex> youth</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wherein the <qex>pregnant</qex> enemy does much.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pregnant construction</b></col> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>,
<cd>one in which more is implied than is said; as, the beasts
<xex>trembled forth</xex> from their dens, that is, came forth trembling
with fright.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pregnant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pregnant
<hw>Preg"nant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A pregnant woman.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pregnant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Pregnant
<hw>Preg"nant</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>prenant</ets> taking.
Cf. <er>Pregnable</er>.]</ety> <def>Affording entrance; receptive;
yielding; willing; open; prompt.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧
<xex>Pregnant</xex> to good pity.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pregnantly</ent>⟦br⟧
